# imports
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import re
import json 

def scraper(url: str) -> str:
  # scraper logic
  job_listings = []
  response = requests.get(url) # get page content
  if response.status_code == 200:
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # parse HTML
    job_listing_divs = soup.find_all('div', attrs={'class': 'posting'}) # find all job listing divs
    for job_listing in job_listing_divs:
      title = job_listing.find('h5', attrs={'data-qa': 'posting-name'}).getText().strip() # find job title
      tag = job_listing.find('span', attrs={'class': 'small-category-label'}).getText().strip() # find tag
      apply_link = job_listing.find('a', attrs={'class': 'posting-btn-submit', 'href': re.compile('/jobs.lever.co/')}).get('href') # find apply link
      job_listings.append({'title': title, 'tag': tag, 'apply_link': apply_link}) # append job listing to list
  return json.dumps(job_listings) # return job listings as JSON

if __name__ == '__main__':
  url = "https://jobs.lever.co/appboxo"
  print(scraper(url))
